Step 1: Calculate the Quick Assets. These include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable.  
  Cash on Hand = 2,067,352.98  
  Bank Deposits = 3,752,082.80  
  Interest Receivable = 12,737.96  
  Accounts Receivable = 321,015.98  
Total Quick Assets = 2,067,352.98 + 3,752,082.80 + 12,737.96 + 321,015.98 = 6,153,189.72

Step 2: Identify Current Liabilities.  
  Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91

Step 3: Compute the Quick Ratio.  
  Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
  Quick Ratio = 6,153,189.72 / 7,605,149.91 ≈ 0.81

Step 4: Calculate the Net Profit Margin.  
  Net Profit = 112,375.10  
  Total Revenue = 775,598.77  
  Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  Net Profit Margin = (112,375.10 / 775,598.77) × 100 ≈ 14.49%

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "0.81", 
    "Net Profit Margin": "14.49%"
  }
}
